%% Streaming rehydration: a placeholder split across chunk boundaries is
%% held back only as long as it stays a viable token prefix, then restored.
%% The same channel machinery serves SSE, NDJSON, Bedrock eventstream
%% frames, and realtime WebSocket deltas.
%% Render: scripts/render_diagrams.sh (PNG committed next to this source).
sequenceDiagram
    participant L as Provider (SSE)
    participant P as Proxy — StreamingRehydrator
    participant T as Agentic tool

    L-->>P: delta "Sent it to «EM"
    Note right of P: "«EM" is a viable token prefix —<br/>hold it back, forward the rest
    P-->>T: delta "Sent it to "
    L-->>P: delta "AIL_001» a mom"
    Note right of P: buffer + chunk = "«EMAIL_001» a mom"<br/>complete token → vault lookup
    P-->>T: delta "jane@corp.example a mom"
    L-->>P: delta "ent ago."
    P-->>T: delta "ent ago."
    L-->>P: content_block_stop
    Note right of P: any held-back leftover flushes as a<br/>synthetic delta BEFORE the stop event
    P-->>T: content_block_stop
    Note over L,T: Chunk-split sweeps test every possible split offset:<br/>streamed output must equal non-streaming output, byte for byte.
